CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 13, 1957, pg. 2, reads: "Ended 'Fourth' - Marlene and Darlene, twin daughters of Mr. and Mrs. Jerome Griggs of 7417 Monticello St., were the last of new babies to arrive at Montefiore Hospital on the Fourth of July, Nurse Bullock is shown with the happy mother who holds Marlene, who weighed five pounds six ounces when born at 10:52 P.M., and Darlene, who arrived several minutes later and weighed five pounds five ounces. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Jerome Griggs, holding newborn daughters Marlene Griggs and Darlene Griggs, posed with nurse Bullock in Montefiore Hospital, Pittsburgh
